## Commit & Push Workflow (Order Matters)

| What changed | Branch | When |
|-------------|--------|------|
| **Game code** (Lua, C++, scripts, content) | `Main` or `Ender_FeatureName` | **First** — commit and push before touching dev env |
| **Dev env** (rules, skills, `.cursor/`, context docs) | `Ender_CursorConfig` only | **Last** — after code is committed and pushed |

Before committing: confirm which branch you are on. Do not mix game code and dev env in the same commit.

---

## Git / Collab (All Machines)

1. Branch naming: `[DeveloperName]_[FeatureName]` (e.g. `Ender_MandalorianWay`)
2. No PRs — push branch and notify Miphstoe or Hellguard in Discord for manual review
3. Test on a WSL machine (Main Desktop or Laptop) before committing
4. Never commit `bin/conf/config.lua`, `ghoutput.xml`, or `resource_manager_spawns.lua` — gitignored

---

## Code Style & Patterns

- C++17 standard
- Use `String` (engine type) not `std::string` for game strings
- Lua scripts in `bin/scripts/` — hot-reloadable without rebuild
- Manager classes follow `ManagerImplementation.cpp` pattern
- Use `info()`, `error()`, `warning()` (Logger methods) — not `printf`/`cout`
- Thread safety: `std::lock_guard<std::mutex>` — mutexes are static file-scope in implementation files

